{
  "text": "For this choice of parameters and λ = 1/2, the Cordes condition (2.7a) is satisfied for ε = 0.0024 (cf. [CITATION_1] ). Let δ = 0.01 and f α = A α : D 2 u + b α · ∇ − c α u, where the exact solution is u(x) = (2x 1 − 1) exp(1 − |2x 1 − 1|) − 1 x 2 + 1 − exp(x 2 /δ) exp(1/δ) − 1 . This solution exhibits a sharp boundary layer near the lineΩ ∩ {x 2 = 1}. Following [CITATION_2] , we use a sequence of graded bisection meshes {T } ∈N0 with grading factor 1/2, see Figure 6a for example. More precisely, we mark the element T whose |T | > C(x 2,T − 1) 2 /#T , where x 2,T is the second component of barycenter of the element T , #T is the number of elements in T . In the experiment, we set C = 120, and use the 2D Hermite finite element spaces for polynomial degrees k = 3. In Figure 6b , we plot the errors in broken H 2 -seminorm, H 1 -seminorm and L 2 on the graded bisection meshes, against the number of degrees of freedom (ndof). We observe a reduction in the order of error O(ndof −1 ), which confirms the second-order convergence as shown in Theorem 5.3. ",
